<p><b>What are the 4 key aspects of innovation management?</b> There are four key pillars to innovation management: Competency, Structure, Culture, and Strategy. As any new idea can be viewed as innovation, it helps to have these pillars in mind to stay organized.</p>
<p><b>What is the difference between innovation and innovation management?</b> Innovation drives business growth and helps organizations stay ahead of their competitors. Innovation management helps generate new business models and creates new products, services and technologies designed for the changing market.</p>
<p><b>Is an innovation in management practices?</b> Innovation management not only focuses on developing new products but also on improving internal processes and operations. It encourages employees to find innovative solutions to streamline workflows, optimize resource allocation, and enhance productivity.</p>
