<p><b>What is the difference between strategic management and innovation management?</b> A strategy is a well-planned series of efforts directed towards attaining a long-term objective or an overall goal. And innovation management is the practice of inspiring, managing and directing an organization's innovation processes from the beginning of ideation to the end of implementation.</p>
<p><b>What is the difference between idea management and innovation management?</b> Idea Management starts with an idea found by somebody who internally brings the idea to the business managers for review and implementation. Innovation Management involves the implementation of innovation into a business model, usually through structured strategy and creative processes such as brainstorming sessions.</p>
<p><b>What is the difference between technology management and innovation management?</b> Comparative Overview: - Focus: Technology Management has a more specific focus on technology as a key resource, while Innovation Management has a broader scope that includes all types of innovation (technological, process, service, and business model innovations).</p>
